I was struggling with this recently and found it surprising that there is no straightforward way to achieve this functionality. I even opened an [issue][2] with Spring Boot, but the feature was deemed too complex to implement.

Nevertheless, I&#39;ve made a proof of concept that supports multiple Spring profiles, precedence and variable interpolation together with ENV variable overriding. It&#39;s not the cleanest and doesn&#39;t mirror Spring Boot entirely, but it should have you covered for most cases. This is how I integrated it in my build.gradle file:

```groovy
import org.springframework.core.env.StandardEnvironment
import org.springframework.core.io.support.PathMatchingResourcePatternResolver
